#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Appify 3.0.0 - PyQt6 Port with Griffin Dark Theme

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
NEW in 3.0.0
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- PYQT6 PORT: Full rewrite of the UI layer from GTK4/libadwaita to PyQt6.
  All logic is identical; only the UI toolkit changed.
- GRIFFIN DARK THEME: UI styled to match the rest of Griffin's UI colors, deep navy
  backgrounds, blue accents.
- LAUNCH BUTTON: Test any installed app directly from the manager without
  leaving the window. The button is disabled until the selected app is installed.
- STORE.JSON: Appify now uses a data-driven application catalog. New apps and 
   extension  presets can be added without requiring an Appify update. The official 
   catalog is protected using  GitHub CODEOWNERS to ensure changes are reviewed 
   before being merged.

- KNOWN ISSUES: 
   1. Some toolbar icons and menu buttons may appear slightly smaller than intended when 
   using the Griffin Dark Theme. This is a cosmetic issue caused by differences between GTK4 
   and PyQt6 stylesheet rendering and does not affect functionality.

   2. Xbox's XCLOUD has an issue with third-party gamepads in any Chromium browser.
   This appears to be a limitation of Xbox Cloud Gaming in Chromium-based browsers rather than 
   Appify. Existing community workarounds, including Better xCloud, have not fully resolved the issue.

- FIXED: Opening the Firefox extension store (or adding a custom extension) for an
  already-running app could incorrectly report "Firefox is already running, but is
  not responding" and never open. The store/extension launcher now remotes the URL
  into the app's existing window when it's already open, and clears out stale
  profile locks left behind by a crash or unclean shutdown when it isn't.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
CARRIED FORWARD FROM 2.2.3
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- CONFIG DIR MIGRATION: ~/.pwa_manager renamed to ~/.appify.
- EXPORT / IMPORT: Export zips ~/.appify; import extracts and regenerates wrappers.
- CATEGORIES: 11 categories with collapsible browser panel and ✓ installed markers.
- PROFILE SIZE INDICATOR: Async on-disk size display.
- REGENERATE ALL WRAPPERS: Hamburger menu action.
- BACKUP EXTENSION WARNING: Lists extensions before backup.
- INTELLIGENT BROWSER DETECTION, WAYLAND/X11 NATIVE SUPPORT,
  8 Browsers, WebHID gamepad, GPU acceleration, nice/ionice per-app, and more.
"""

